@startuml
!include _yunlink_protocol_theme.iuml
title Yunlink Test World Map - Test Pyramid

rectangle "Release confidence" <<Neutral>> {
  rectangle "HIL / Real Vehicle Safety Gate\nmissing" as L6 <<Risk>>
  rectangle "PX4 SITL + Sunray + Bridge + Ground\nmissing" as L5 <<Risk>>
  rectangle "Long Soak / Weak Network Matrix\nscaffolded, not proven" as L4 <<Risk>>
  rectangle "Dual-host Semantic Suites\nbaseline / recovery / competition / routing / scale" as L3 <<StatePlane>>
  rectangle "Single-host Interop and SDK Matrix\nRust / Python / C++" as L2 <<StatePlane>>
  rectangle "Runtime / Transport / ABI Tests\npartial strong" as L1 <<Control>>
  rectangle "Protocol Codec / Parser Unit Tests\nstrongest current base" as L0 <<Control>>
}

L6 -down-> L5
L5 -down-> L4
L4 -down-> L3
L3 -down-> L2
L2 -down-> L1
L1 -down-> L0

note right of L5
This is the largest reason
business coverage is still ~32/100.
end note

note left of L3
Office Wi-Fi dual-host suites
prove important network semantics,
but not real flight execution.
end note
@enduml
